    "source": "---\nlocale: en\ntitle: \"Insulin-smart over calorie counting\"\nslug: \"insulin-smart-over-calorie-counting\"\nexcerpt: \"A framework for hunger & choice beats constant tracking.\"\ncategory: \"Metabolism\"\ntags: [\"Insulin\", \"Nutrition\"]\nreadingTime: 7\nauthor: \"Livalance\"\npublished: true\npublishDate: \"2024-04-15\"\ncover: \"/images/articles/insulin-smart.svg\"\nseoTitle: \"Insulin-smart over calorie counting\"\nseoDescription: \"Stabilise signals and make decisions easier without logging every gram.\"\n---\n\n## Insulin sets the tone\n\nChronically elevated insulin keeps fat locked, cravings loud, and choices reactive. Calorie math matters, but an insulin-smart structure makes it livable.\n\n## Five levers\n\n1. **Sequencing** – Fiber first, then protein/fat, starch last.\n2. **Protein + fiber** – 30 g protein plus crunch slows the curve.\n3. **Meal breaks** – Start with 12:12, flex up to 14:10 or 16:8 as life allows.\n4. **Strength + NEAT** – ≤15-min kettlebells and more steps raise insulin sensitivity.\n5. **Stress hygiene** – Down-regulate at night; less cortisol means better glucose.\n\n## Apply it\n\nPick two meals this week to re-engineer. Rate energy & cravings daily (1–5). Iterate, don’t obsess.\n"
