    "source": "---\nlocale: en\ntitle: \"Unwind Faster: 4 Evening Rituals for Deep Sleep\"\nslug: \"unwind-evening-rituals\"\nexcerpt: \"Light, breath, journaling, and magnesium help your nervous system release the day.\"\ncategory: \"Sleep\"\ntags:\n  - \"Sleep\"\n  - \"Routine\"\nreadingTime: 5\nauthor: \"Livalance\"\npublished: true\npublishDate: \"2024-02-10\"\ncover: \"/images/articles/evening-rituals.svg\"\nseoTitle: \"Unwind Faster – Evening Rituals for Restorative Sleep | Livalance\"\nseoDescription: \"Four micro-habits to signal safety, calm the body, and drift off with ease.\"\n---\n\n# Evening Rituals That Stick\n\nGood sleep is a 24-hour practice. These four rituals ease you into rest without adding complexity.\n\n## Dim the Light\n\nSwap bright overhead lighting for warm, indirect lamps or candles after 8 pm to support melatonin.\n\n## Extend Your Exhale\n\nPractice the 4-7-8 breath or simply double the length of your exhale to calm your vagus nerve.\n\n## Close the Loop\n\nTake three minutes to jot down wins, loose ends, and gratitude. Putting thoughts on paper clears cognitive clutter.\n\n## Add Magnesium\n\nMagnesium glycinate or a mineral bath relaxes muscles and signals your body to soften.\n\n## Build the Habit\n\nAttach the ritual to an existing routine—after brushing your teeth or tidying the kitchen—to make it automatic.\n"
